        "title": "Doctor: expose dry-run preview reports",
        "body": "## Stack Refresh\n\nRestacked on #84450 after the Doctor note policy simplification.\n\nCurrent parent: #84450 (`doctor-cron-audit-structured-repairs`).\nCurrent head is a single commit on top of that parent.\n\n## Contract Notes\n\nThis PR follows the refreshed structured Doctor contract:\n\n```ts\ndetect(ctx, scope?) -> HealthFinding[]\nrepair(ctx, findings) -> HealthRepairResult\n```\n\nFindings are machine/CI/lint signal. Human presentation uses `ctx.doctor.note(message, title?)`. Preview JSON intentionally does not include detection/repair note arrays; it reports findings, changes, warnings, effects, diffs, and skipped unconverted contributions.\n\n## Scope\n\nAdds top-level `doctor --dry-run`, `--diff`, and JSON preview reporting for structured doctor repairs, with explicit skipped records for unconverted repair contributions.\n\n## Verification\n\n- Restacked on refreshed #84450 and squashed to one commit.\n- Confirmed by code search that this branch does not reintroduce `HealthPresentationNote`, `repairNote`, `detectionNotes`, `repairNotes`, preview note arrays, or structured note result surfaces.\n- `git diff --check` passed.\n- No focused test rerun completed in this local worktree; use fresh CI for broad proof.\r\n",
